ML1 is a language that defines events that
occur in time, and it uses two fundamental temporal abstractions --
concurrency and sequentiality.  The ML1 "chord" operator is really a
generalized concurrency notation, and ML1 sequences define events that
occur one after another.  ML1 allows mixing of these two very
fundamental notions in a structured way. 


